text: Fremont County is a county in the U.S. state of Wyoming. In the 2020 census, 39,234 people lived there. Its county seat is Lander. The county was formed in 1884. It is named for John C. Fr√©mont, a general, explorer, and politician. It is about the size of the state of Vermont.
